<Link id="l00838" /><CodeLine lineNumber="838"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// Refines the subranges to support \\p LaneMask. This may only be called</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00839" /><CodeLine lineNumber="839"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// for LI.hasSubrange()==true. Subregister ranges are split or created</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00840" /><CodeLine lineNumber="840"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// until \\p LaneMask can be matched exactly. \\p Mod is executed on the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00841" /><CodeLine lineNumber="841"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// matching subranges.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00842" /><CodeLine lineNumber="842"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00843" /><CodeLine lineNumber="843"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// Example:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00844" /><CodeLine lineNumber="844"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///    Given an interval with subranges with lanemasks L0F00, L00F0 and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00845" /><CodeLine lineNumber="845"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///    L000F, refining for mask L0018. Will split the L00F0 lane into</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00846" /><CodeLine lineNumber="846"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///    L00E0 and L0010 and the L000F lane into L0007 and L0008. The Mod</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00847" /><CodeLine lineNumber="847"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///    function will be applied to the L0010 and L0008 subranges.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00848" /><CodeLine lineNumber="848"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00849" /><CodeLine lineNumber="849"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// \\p Indexes and \\p TRI are required to clean up the VNIs that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00850" /><CodeLine lineNumber="850"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// don&#39;t define the related lane masks after they get shrunk. E.g.,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00851" /><CodeLine lineNumber="851"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// when L000F gets split into L0007 and L0008 maybe only a subset</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00852" /><CodeLine lineNumber="852"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// of the VNIs that defined L000F defines L0007.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00853" /><CodeLine lineNumber="853"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00854" /><CodeLine lineNumber="854"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// The clean up of the VNIs need to look at the actual instructions</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00855" /><CodeLine lineNumber="855"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// to decide what is or is not live at a definition point. If the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00856" /><CodeLine lineNumber="856"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// update of the subranges occurs while the IR does not reflect these</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00857" /><CodeLine lineNumber="857"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// changes, \\p ComposeSubRegIdx can be used to specify how the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00858" /><CodeLine lineNumber="858"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// definition are going to be rewritten.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00859" /><CodeLine lineNumber="859"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// E.g., let say we want to merge:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00860" /><CodeLine lineNumber="860"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///     V1.sub1:&lt;2 x s32&gt; = COPY V2.sub3:&lt;4 x s32&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00861" /><CodeLine lineNumber="861"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// We do that by choosing a class where sub1:&lt;2 x s32&gt; and sub3:&lt;4 x s32&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00862" /><CodeLine lineNumber="862"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// overlap, i.e., by choosing a class where we can find &quot;offset + 1 == 3&quot;.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00863" /><CodeLine lineNumber="863"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// Put differently we align V2&#39;s sub3 with V1&#39;s sub1:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00864" /><CodeLine lineNumber="864"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// V2: sub0 sub1 sub2 sub3</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00865" /><CodeLine lineNumber="865"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// V1: &lt;offset&gt;  sub0 sub1</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00866" /><CodeLine lineNumber="866"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00867" /><CodeLine lineNumber="867"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// This offset will look like a composed subregidx in the class:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00868" /><CodeLine lineNumber="868"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///     V1.(composed sub2 with sub1):&lt;4 x s32&gt; = COPY V2.sub3:&lt;4 x s32&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00869" /><CodeLine lineNumber="869"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// =&gt;  V1.(composed sub2 with sub1):&lt;4 x s32&gt; = COPY V2.sub3:&lt;4 x s32&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00870" /><CodeLine lineNumber="870"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00871" /><CodeLine lineNumber="871"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// Now if we didn&#39;t rewrite the uses and def of V1, all the checks for V1</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00872" /><CodeLine lineNumber="872"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// need to account for this offset.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00873" /><CodeLine lineNumber="873"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// This happens during coalescing where we update the live-ranges while</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00874" /><CodeLine lineNumber="874"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// still having the old IR around because updating the IR on-the-fly</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00875" /><CodeLine lineNumber="875"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// would actually clobber some information on how the live-ranges that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00876" /><CodeLine lineNumber="876"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// are being updated look like.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00877" /><CodeLine lineNumber="877"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liveinterval/#a967540f5e5799b56c6fbcee378d110eb">refineSubRanges</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a8e612822d4ba7bb36c9c79582a567108">BumpPtrAllocator</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/regallocbasic-cpp/#ad5d00e1d77644d95847b9bf8da12b759">Allocator</a>, <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/lanebitmask">LaneBitmask</a> LaneMask,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00878" /><CodeLine lineNumber="878"><Highlight kind="normal">                         std::function&lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liveinterval/subrange">LiveInterval::SubRange</a> &amp;)&gt; Apply,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00879" /><CodeLine lineNumber="879"><Highlight kind="normal">                         </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/slotindexes">SlotIndexes</a> &amp;Indexes,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00880" /><CodeLine lineNumber="880"><Highlight kind="normal">                         </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetregisterinfo">TargetRegisterInfo</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/machinesink-cpp/#a0f36ed1bc17fc1aa97fe291c439a0698">TRI</a>,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00881" /><CodeLine lineNumber="881"><Highlight kind="normal">                         </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ComposeSubRegIdx = 0);</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00937" /><CodeLine lineNumber="937"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Calling LiveRange::addSegment() repeatedly can be expensive on large</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00943" /><CodeLine lineNumber="943" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liverangeupdater"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liverangeupdater/#a7f8850300c47772d8ae8a70aab6b1996">LiveRangeUpdater</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
